Elgeyo Marakwet farmers stare at losses as rains damage roads             Stephen Rutto  11th Sep 2019 09:30:45 GMT +0300 Stephen Rutto  11th Sep 2019 09:30:45 GMT +0300 Stephen Rutto   Lorries get stuck along Kaptalamwa-Kapyego Road in Elgeyo Marakwet County following heavy rains in the area. Farmers in the area say they are staring at losses after transport got paralysed. [Stephen Rutto, Standard]  Lorries get stuck along Kaptalamwa-Kapyego Road in Elgeyo Marakwet County following heavy rains in the area. Farmers in the area say they are staring at losses after transport got paralysed. [Stephen Rutto, Standard] Lorries get stuck along Kaptalamwa-Kapyego Road in Elgeyo Marakwet County following heavy rains in the area. Farmers in the area say they are staring at losses after transport got paralysed. [Stephen Rutto, Standard] Lorries get stuck along Kaptalamwa-Kapyego Road in Elgeyo Marakwet County following heavy rains in the area. Farmers in the area say they are staring at losses after transport got paralysed      SEE ALSO :EX-MP children directed to end Sh500m tussle SEE ALSO : EX-MP children directed to end Sh500m tussle    For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   SEE ALSO :Residents threaten to boycott national census SEE ALSO : Residents threaten to boycott national census   We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. HERE Related Topics Elgeyo Marakwet North Rift Farmers